        "generateUrl": "https://docs.cloud.google.com/dns/docs/authentication",
        "setup": "Follow [Authenticate to Cloud DNS](https://docs.cloud.google.com/dns/docs/authentication). The easiest path for local development is to install the Google Cloud CLI and run [`gcloud auth application-default login`](https://cloud.google.com/sdk/gcloud/reference/auth/application-default/login) or [`gcloud auth login`](https://cloud.google.com/sdk/gcloud/reference/auth/login) to obtain Google-issued OAuth 2.0 credentials. For production, create a service account in [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/), grant Cloud DNS/IAM roles, and use Application Default Credentials to mint bearer tokens with scopes such as `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/ndev.clouddns.readwrite`, `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/ndev.clouddns.readonly`, `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform`, or `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform.read-only`.",
